<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">AilenGoldenfire_Quellious</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If we forget about all the "kiling your god is bad" arguments, and look at PoG for high elves, is it worth it to keep the faction?<P>So far the only thing i can see that comes from PoG for a High Elf cleric is the bracer of tunarian worship. If you compare this one piece (which is quite hard to get in itself) to how easy it is to get pieces of stability armor, is there any point in saving your faction?<P>------------------<BR>Ailen Goldenfire<BR>Cleric of the Council of Arcana<BR>Quellious<BR>"A fool think himself wise, but a wise man knows himself a fool."</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Auelan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm personally keeping mine. Not only is it helpful for a rez stick to have good faction up there for the possible wipe out, but Stability is about the same as Forbidden Rites, which is just as easy to get, imo. Besides, that is quite a nice bracer.<P>Auelan Lifebringer<BR>57th season Templar of Tunare<BR>Enshadowed<BR>Brell Serilis server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wisecleric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">"So far the only thing i can see that comes from PoG for a High Elf cleric is the bracer of tunarian worship."<P>The key words here are "So far..." <P>Who knows what is to come? At this point i would not risk losing the faction personally, due to the lack of knowledge of exactly what you gain AND what you lose.<P>Looking into the next expansion, there will be ways to advance your character other than killing creatures for experience. Who knows what that might entail? For clerics it might involve some heavy faction work. Sure im grabbing at straws, but still, something to think about. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Urzak</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hey there, Ailen<P>Do you plan on doing any cultural smithing?  If I'm correct, high elves need to use their racial forge (conveniently located in Felwithe  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif">) to combine the ingredients.<P>Let's also remember that the world is not static.  It would be really unfortunate to see new content added in the future that is dependent on your faction.<P>Urzak<BR>Quellious</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">With my luck, as soon as I trash my faction, Verant will put in a whole slew of great quests for Tunare worshippers that result in uber gear and of course the cleric stuff would start in the guild in Felwithe... so I'm going to keep my faction. So much HIE CLR Tunare gear sucks bad that I don't want to trash the possibility of good stuff in the future. And of course there is that bracer I want as well.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mahtan Honorshield</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">But Jubal, if you DON'T screw up faction there will never be any new Tunare quests in PoG...you're just doing it to spite us other Tunare clerics, admit it! :-)<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
